Prevalence of Low Vehicle Access

This is a map of low vehicle access. Low vehicle households were defined as households without a vehicle and with no supermarkets within 1/2 mile. Low vehicle census tracts were defined as census tracts with > 100 low vehicle access households.

food_access <-
  read_csv("/Users/armellecoutant/Documents/GitHub/218z/SNAP/DataDownload2015.csv")
low_vehicle <-
  food_access %>%
  dplyr::select(CensusTract, State, County, HUNVFlag)

low_vehicle <-
  low_vehicle %>%
  group_by(State) %>%
  summarise(
    HUNVFlag = sum(HUNVFlag)
  )

low_vehicle_by_state <-
  low_vehicle %>%
  inner_join(state_laea, by = c("State" = "STATE")) %>%
  st_as_sf()

tm_shape(low_vehicle_by_state) +
tm_polygons(col = "HUNVFlag", legend.hist = TRUE, border.col = "white") +
tm_layout(main.title = "Low Vehicle Access (Still Needs to be Normalized by State Population)", main.title.size = 1, legend.outside = TRUE, legend.title.color = "white", legend.title.size = 0.0001, legend.hist.width = 1)

Prevalence of Food Deserts

This is a map of the prevalence of food deserts by state. Low food access was defined as having no supermarkets within 1 mile for urban areas and within 10 miles for rural areas.

low_food <-
  food_access %>%
  dplyr::select(CensusTract, State, County, LA1and10)

low_food <-
  low_food %>%
  group_by(State) %>%
  summarise(
    LA1and10 = sum(LA1and10)
  )

low_food_by_state <-
  low_food %>%
  inner_join(state_laea, by = c("State" = "STATE")) %>%
  st_as_sf()

tm_shape(low_food_by_state) +
tm_polygons(col = "LA1and10", legend.hist = TRUE, border.col = "white") +
tm_layout(main.title = "Prevalence of Food Deserts by State (Still Needs to be Normalized by State Population)", main.title.size = 1, legend.outside = TRUE, legend.title.color = "white", legend.title.size = 0.0001, legend.hist.width = 1)
